<div class="ndx-hero-callout">
  <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Why this matters</h3>
  <p class="govuk-body">
    Easy Read is a format that makes information accessible to people with learning disabilities.
    It uses simple words, short sentences, and images to support understanding. In the UK,
    approximately 1.5 million people have a learning disability, and councils have a legal
    duty under the Equality Act 2010 to make information accessible.
  </p>
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
    Traditional Easy Read production costs around <strong>&pound;120 per page</strong> and takes weeks.
    Simply Readable does it for approximately <strong>1p per page</strong> in minutes -- making it
    practical for councils to make <em>all</em> their documents accessible, not just the most critical ones.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Creating an Easy Read document</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Navigate to Readable</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      From the dashboard, click <strong>"Readable"</strong> in the sidebar navigation.
      Then click <strong>"Create Readable"</strong> or the equivalent button.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Upload your document</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Upload a <code>.docx</code> document. For the best demonstration, use a document with
      formal or complex language -- a policy document, a council notice, or a letter about
      services. The more complex the source, the more impressive the simplification.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Start the Easy Read conversion</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click <strong>"Create"</strong> or <strong>"Submit"</strong>. This triggers a more
      complex Step Functions workflow than translation.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Watch the AI at work</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The dashboard will show the job progressing through multiple stages. This takes longer
      than translation because it involves multiple AI steps:
    </p>

    <div class="ndx-ai-pipeline">
      <div class="ndx-ai-pipeline__step">
        <span class="ndx-ai-pipeline__number">1</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Text extraction</strong>
          <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">The document text is extracted and structured</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ndx-ai-pipeline__step">
        <span class="ndx-ai-pipeline__number">2</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Text simplification (Claude 3 Haiku)</strong>
          <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">Amazon Bedrock uses Claude 3 Haiku to rewrite the text in plain language with short sentences</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ndx-ai-pipeline__step">
        <span class="ndx-ai-pipeline__number">3</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Image generation (Nova Canvas)</strong>
          <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">AI generates supporting images for each section to aid understanding</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ndx-ai-pipeline__step">
        <span class="ndx-ai-pipeline__number">4</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Document assembly</strong>
          <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">The simplified text and images are combined into an Easy Read format</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Review the result</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Once complete, click on the job to view the Easy Read output. You will see:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li><strong>Simplified text</strong> -- complex language rewritten in plain, short sentences</li>
      <li><strong>Supporting images</strong> -- AI-generated illustrations that reinforce the meaning</li>
      <li><strong>Clear layout</strong> -- large text, plenty of white space, one idea per section</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Co-created with Experts by Experience</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Simply Readable was not built in isolation. Swindon Borough Council worked with
  "Experts by Experience" -- people with learning disabilities who reviewed and
  shaped the Easy Read output. Their feedback directly influenced how the AI
  simplifies text and what kinds of images are generated.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
  This co-creation approach ensures the output genuinely meets the needs of the people
  it is designed for, rather than being based on assumptions about what "simple" means.
</p>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
    <strong>98% community satisfaction:</strong> In user testing with people with learning
    disabilities, 98% rated the AI-generated Easy Read documents as helpful and easy to understand.
  </p>
</div>

